The paper presents a novel algorithm for reciprocal collision avoidance between heterogeneous agents, which is a problem commonly studied in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm uses a CTMAT representation based on medial axis transform, which involves computational geometry techniques (cs.CG). The paper also mentions the use of linear programming and precomputing Minkowski Sums, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The algorithm's performance is evaluated on benchmarks corresponding to road traffic scenarios, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV).
